- The string parameter `sentence` must not be null.
- The integer result is the number of valid words in the sentence.
- A valid word in the sentence must meet the following criteria:
    - It only contains lowercase letters, hyphens, and/or punctuation marks (no digits).
    - There is at most one hyphen, and if present, it must be surrounded by lowercase characters.
    - There is at most one punctuation mark, and if present, it must be at the end of the token.